{{Use New Zealand English|date=November 2016}}
'''Hugo Friedlander''' (1850 &ndash; 1 October 1928) was a New Zealand businessman and politician. He was born in [[Chodzież|Kolmar]], in the Prussian Province of Posen in 1850. He was the second [[Mayor of Ashburton, New Zealand|Mayor of Ashburton]].<ref name="DNZB Friedlander">{{DNZB|McCausland|Ray|2f28|Hugo Friedlander|1 December 2011}}</ref> He co-owned the ''[[Ashburton Guardian]]'' from 1880 to 1885.<ref>{{cite web | title=Ashburton Guardian | url=http://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/cgi-bin/paperspast?a=d&cl=CL1.AG&essay=1 | publisher=PapersPast | accessdate=6 June 2015}}</ref> He left for [[Auckland]] in 1918 due to anti-German feelings caused by World War I.<ref name="DNZB Friedlander" />

